I can't reproduce, but I will look into alternatives to using an ArrayList.
*** Bug 92284 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
*** Bug 94052 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***
I have a workbench I can send you that this happens a lot with.

We were still unable to reproduce even with Tod's workspace.
So we had a summit and determined that these ArrayOutOfBoundExceptions can 
occur if mutliple threads are messing with member variables.

So instead of keeping the resolved classpath in a member ArrayList variable as 
we compute it, we first compute it in a local variable and then copy its 
content at the end as an array to the member variable.

Tod, please give I-20050512-1739 a try and verify that your (build) problems 
have gone away.
